title: Manhattan: Hudson Street.

text:
Hudson Street, west side, at Grove Street, showing St. Lukes P.E. Chapel; cornerstone laid June 4, 1821. To the right are 3 story structures that extend to Christopher Street. The parish house is the first of these, occupying a double frontage. This photo was reproduced on page 96 of the published volume "Changing New York."

June 18, 1936

Berenice Abbott, photo

Street Scenes - Manhattan: A milk wagon on a Greenwich Village route. Buildings to the rear are No's 4 to 10 Grove Street. Adjoining the latter (left) is the entrance to an interior garden row of dwellings identified as Grove Court. This is not shown.

June 18, 1936
